Soundscape Narrative  
My soundscape narrative centers around a vital part of my daily routine, my morning coffee. Coffee has always been more than just a drink for my mom and I, it was a ritual we shared and a special moment for us. Whether it was a rushed and busy morning getting ready for school or a slow weekend morning, we would share that moment together. It was a grounding and comforting routine that I have many fond memories of. Making coffee is something that so many people do on a daily basis, yet everyone has their own kind of routine of how they do it. It is interesting to see the difference in how such a simple task is done and how simple actions carry emotional weight.   
In creating this soundscape, I wanted a blend of different audios to create a warm and inviting environment. The main focus of the soundscape is the sound of the coffee itself being made.

I captured the audio of making coffee in a single take to ensure I captured every sound that I thought would be pleasing and interesting to the ear. I then split this clip up into each of the steps, getting rid of the unnecessary audio between steps and allowing me to isolate and enhance sounds. The brewing of the coffee was much louder than the other steps, so to make the audio smoother, I had to amplify some clips and reduce the volume of others. The sounds of the clinking of the ice, pouring the coffee into the glass, adding the creamer, and stirring up the drink follow the brewing. Though quick and subtle, these sounds are satisfying and provide insight into the specific routine I follow when making coffee.

To replicate the interaction and conversations my mom and I would share during this time, I incorporated and layered audio clips of laughter and soft talking to add a sense of intimacy to the soundscape. I chose two different audio clips of laughter to add depth and create a sense of a genuine exchange between two people. I did not want the dialogue of the conversation to be distinguishable, so I found an audio that captured the tone and warmth of casual conversation. It was not the words that were important but rather the feeling it conveyed.

	I incorporated a suggestion from my peer feedback to add soft music in the background, and It truly felt like the missing piece that completed the soundscape. The music enhanced the warm and cozy atmosphere I was aiming to create, and provided a subtle emotional layer. To ensure the music flowed seamlessly with the audio, I split it up into three sections. In the beginning of the soundscape, where the coffee machine is brewing loudly, I let the music be in its original form to complement the movement. The following clips were quieter and I wanted to ensure you could hear the satisfying sounds of the coffee being made, so I made the rest of the audio quieter. Finally, I chose to fade out the music at the end to create a smoother conclusion rather than an abrupt ending.   
The overall goal with this soundscape narrative was to recreate the feeling and environment that I experienced of making coffee with my mom in the mornings. I wanted to immerse the listener into the experience through the sounds of making the coffee, and by setting the mood with laughter, conversation, and music.
